metadata.name: Harlequins #92
metadata.description:
Harlequins

---

WebGL2, a fast GPU will make it more enjoyable. There's an initial pre-compute phase for the animation and that can pause a slow GPU for a few seconds.

---

Harlequins is an exploration in generating beautiful color and texture out of often-discordant beginnings. Much like our world.

Each Harlequin has random materials, background, and a random number of moons around it. Each frame adds more painted light and turns the initial harsh scene into a dreamlike blending of color, creating smooth matte colors on the central orb.

Harlequins is the result of a few months of generative work and lookdev on top of older long-exposure path tracing shaders. The runner and custom WebGL lib are written in TypeScript, lot of GLSL for the fragment shaders, then the whole thing is compiled, minified, and inlined into the final single self-contained HTML file. 6.4k zipped.


Ilmari Heikkinen 2022. Have fun.

---

Press space to enter the display mode. The display mode generates infinite new variants of your minted scene, displaying each one for a short while. Great for chilling out for a bit.

Press s to take a screenshot.

Double-click to render a new variant.

metadata.name: de|growth:generations #34
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: Omega Point #154
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Fax Abstraction #74
metadata.description:
The work was created from neurally generated with Latent Diffusion pictorial abstractions, which I was inspired by the work of Gerhard Richter.
They were further hybridized in the spirit of pointillism and Yayoi Kusama and the vintage fax art aesthetic.
Therefore, this work is about the friendship of different artistic styles coexisting together : )

Thanks Yulikolay for help in its creation!

metadata.name: Phantoms #30
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.
